post_text: Two BHHS seniors presented their research at the virtual National Junior Science and Humanities Symposium on April 15-16, 2020. National JSHS brings together 230 high school students who qualify by submitting and presenting original scientific research papers in regional symposia held at universities nationwide. Owen Skrilloff presented his work to over 20 scientists and won third place in Physical Science. Sam Aberman presented his poster in medicine and health/behavioral sciences and won first place. Congratulations! #sciencerocks #gobyram

post_text: Yesterday, two seniors in the Authentic Science Research Program participated in the Junior Science and Humanities Symposium (JSHS), sharing their work virtually. Having already placed at the regional level in February, each student presented his work to three judges on a phone, competing against eight to nine other students. The day ended with Owen Skriloff and Sam Aberman being awarded first place in their respective “rooms” in Physical & Computational Science and Biochemistry. Congratulations! #sciencerocks #gobyram

post_text:
The Byram Hills Education Foundation will be hosting a free screening of ‘SCREENAGERS NEXT CHAPTER: Uncovering Skills for Stress Resilience’ on Monday, February 10th at 7:30pm at HCC and will be followed by a panel discussion.

This film follows Delaney as she finds herself at a loss on how to help her own teens as they struggle with their emotional wellbeing. She sets out to understand these challenges in our current screen-filled society, and how we, as parents and educators, can empower teens to overcome mental health challenges and build emotional agility, communication savvy, and stress resilience. #socialemotionalhealth

Congratulations to Nora Lowe, BHHS sophomore, who was selected as a national semifinalist for the Mars 2020 ‘Name the Rover’ contest! NASA's Mars 2020 Rover is one step closer to having its own name after 155 students across the U.S. were chosen as semifinalists. Nora’s entry was selected as New York’s winner in the high school category.

The suggested name, Ambition Tardigrada, and Nora’s essay can be viewed here: https://www.futureengineers.org/nametherover/gallery/18307

post_text: On Friday, January 24th Therapy Dogs of Rockland visited high school students during lunch hours. In conjunction with the initiatives of Challenge Success, therapy dogs Bailey, Jessi, and Chuck offered students an opportunity to “Paws & Relax” during the school day. Long established and reliable research shows that animals, especially dogs, have significant effects on human’s comfort and well-being. Therapy dogs will be available to students in Bobcat Hall the fourth Friday of every month. #pawsandrelax #gobyram

post_text: Yesterday, author Alan Katz visited second grader’s at Coman Hill! The children were engaged as they learned about his career and all the various jobs you can do as a writer. Alan visits schools to "share the joys of reading and writing...and sing...and talk about being creative...and discuss how books are made...and inspire everyone to get busy reading and writing and writing and reading!" Alan has written many books including ‘Take Me Out of the Bathtub’, ‘The Day the Mustache Took Over’, and ‘The Day the Mustache Came Back.’ #readingrocks

Three BHHS students were selected to represent the best of the Byram Hills Visual Arts program at StART 2020: 14th Annual Regional High Schools Student Art Exhibition. Awards of Excellence were given to Just Another Day (D.Schwimmer) and Exoskeleton Wings (V. Zawojek). #artmatters #byramhillsarts #byram

post_text:
Two Byram Hills High School students participated in the New York State School Music Association (NYSSMA) All-State program last weekend in Rochester, NY. Nathaniel Bergman ('21) and Grace Byrd ('20) were selected to perform with the All-State Mixed Chorus after receiving top scores on their All-State adjudications. They were chosen from a candidate pool of over 6500 students throughout New York State!

Here is a short clip of a rehearsal where students are working on "Please Stay" by Jake Runestad. This piece is an anthem for hope — an attempt to destigmatize mental illness and challenge all of us to support those who are battling depression. #hope #gobyram

They were chosen from a candidate pool of over 6500 students throughout New York State!

This past Monday, 60 Byram Hills students were inducted into the World Languages Honor Society. This occasion celebrates the hard work and dedication demonstrated throughout their study of another language. The ceremony was extra special with the induction of an honorary member that had his own language journey to share. Carlos Toribio, a Byram Hills senior, started learning English in 2013. He gave a touching and powerful keynote address to a supportive audience of fellow inductees and community members. #félicitations #congratulazioni #felicitaciones #gobyram

Please check out the full Induction Ceremony: www.bobcattv.org/bhhs

post_text: Congratulations to our Track and Field athletes who competed at the state championships over the weekend! Sophomore Jen Mui finished sixth in the state in the 2,000m steeplechase and the boys 4x100 relay team of Spencer Sidoti, Steven Franco, Wylie Troy and Pietro Perez took third and broke the school record with a time of 42.91! Nicole Meyer finished 15th in the state for the 400 hurdles with a time of 1:08.07 and she received the Sportsmanship award. Wylie Troy finished 32nd in the state for high jump, clearing 6 feet. Good luck to Jen Mui, Spencer Sidoti, Steven Franco, Wylie Troy and Pietro Perez, who are competing at the national championships, which begin Thursday in Greensboro, North Carolina. Jen will compete in the 2,000m steeplechase, along with the sprint medley relay team of 100 meters (Spencer) 100 meters (Steven) 200 (Wylie) 400 (Pietro). #ByramPride #ByramAthletics

post_text: Congrats and good luck to these track and field athletes headed to the state championships in Middletown! On Saturday, it’s Jen Mui in the 2000 steeplechase and Wylie Troy in the high jump. Best of luck to you all! #ByramPride #ByramAthletics
